%N A125837 a(n) = 6*(8^n - 1)/7.
%C A125837 Original definition: Numbers whose base 8 or octal representation is 6666666......6.
%C A125837 Also: after 0 and 6, always append the least nonnegative integer not occurring earlier such that the concatenation of the binary representation of all terms is a palindrome. If the initial terms are not imposed, this gives (0, 1, 2, 6, 54, ...). It might be more natural to use offset 0 for both of these sequences. - _M. F. Hasler_, Sep 20 2025
%H A125837 M. F. Hasler, <a href="/A125837/b125837.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a> (initially from _G. C. Greubel_ with offset 1), Sep 26 2025
%H A125837 <a href="/index/Rec#order_02">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (9,-8).
%F A125837 a(n) = 6*(8^n - 1)/7 = 6*A023001(n).
%F A125837 a(n) = 8*a(n-1) + 6 for n>0, a(0) = 0. - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Oct 03 2010
%F A125837 G.f.: 6*x/( (1-x)*(1-8*x) ). - _R. J. Mathar_, Oct 07 2016
%F A125837 E.g.f.: 6*(exp(8*x) - exp(x))/7. - _G. C. Greubel_, Aug 03 2019
%F A125837 a(n) = A083068(n) - 1. - _Alois P. Heinz_, May 20 2023
%p A125837 seq(6*(8^n-1)/7, n=0..30);
